pageContext.claim: “This crime was a -- the crime was committed on the other side, and we'll find out about that. We have a great attorney general who is looking at it. I'm not involved in that.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that "a crime" was committed by the FBI when it launched the investigation in response to a warning from an Australian diplomat who said a Trump campaign official disclosed Russia had obtained damaging information concerning Hillary Clinton.
